title: College of Engineering and Applied Sciences Records

finding_aid_title: College of Engineering and Applied Sciences Records

content: Administrative records of the College, formerly known as the College of Computing and Information, contains programs in Informatics, Computer Science, and Information Studies.
The materials are located onsite in the department.

subnotes.content: The College of Computing and Information (CCI) was originally formed in 2005 from the School of Information Science and Policy and contained the Computer Science and Information Studies departments. In 2015, the school was renamed the College of Engineering and Applied Sciences and a new program in Computer Engineering was developed.

Collection contains administrative records, such as internal assessments, meeting minutes, correspondence, budgetary information, grant proposals, and documentation of events and major programatic changes.
The collection has no series, the original order of the material was kept.

All items in this collection were transferred to the University Libraries, M.E. Grenander Department of Special Collections and Archives by Assistant Dean Nan Carroll.<date normal="2015-08">2015 August</date>

Access to this collection is restricted. Portions of the collection may contain recent administrative records and/or personally identifiable information. Please contact an archivist for more information.
